On the demand side, SPOT has paid + unpaid users, thus its addressable market & the data that comes with it will out scale NFLX. On the supply side, SPOT has all music content available, and not just 10-20% of the video people watch on a daily basis as NFLX does.

Spotify widely considered to have a great recommendation engine, quickly getting the listener to music they like. Compared to NFLX, SPOT has a wider relative funnel on both the demand & supply side, and also has no incentive of what content to favor when making a recommendation.

Biggest challenge for NFLX to solve = curation, which opens a path for a 3rd party using reviews/social media to wedge itself between the viewer, the decision of what to watch, & the content. @SMTPlatitudes looking backwards... NFLX has a better financial model, SPOT has a better user experience; looking forward, SPOT is now copying NFLX's vertical integration (starting w podcasts), & NFLX will prob introduce a free product tier w ads

On the demand side, SPOT has paid + unpaid users, thus its addressable market & the data that comes with it will out scale NFLX. On the supply side, SPOT has all music content available, and not just 10-20% of the video people watch on a daily basis as NFLX does.

Spotify widely considered to have a great recommendation engine, quickly getting the listener to music they like. Compared to NFLX, SPOT has a wider relative funnel on both the demand & supply side, and also has no incentive of what content to favor when making a recommendation.

Biggest challenge for NFLX to solve = curation, which opens a path for a 3rd party using reviews/social media to wedge itself between the viewer, the decision of what to watch, & the content. NFLX's incentive to keep its data private + favor its owned content are related factors. https://t.co/dcZ9zyHVYB

@LibertyRPF @patrick_oshag @SonOfUhGunn in a world of increasing abundance, curation becomes the highest value add in the ecosystem; NFLX realizes this, & probably also see it as one of their biggest threats, thus will not ever be releasing viewing data or APIs to help some 3rd party get up funnel bt NFLX & the viewer
